[center][b]Basic Inspecting[/b][/center]

Basic inspecting is the first thing to do when learning how to inspect code. Basic inspecting contains the basic element of common sense. Now, lets take this simple code for example:

[code]
if(command.equals("fr00b")) {
    forcechat("Me a FR00B!") ;
  }
[/code]

[i]"What does this do?"[/i] starters may ask. However, you are reading this guide, and you're not a starter now. You've taken one step into success.

[b]Get smart![/b]

You know that forcetext forces the player to say this. You know because, you saw in your source a forcetext and tried that command and it forced you to say whatever the command said it would say. See how ts is going? The lovely developers gave you clues, you just have to dig up and find them.

[b]Exercise[/b]

What does this do:

[code]
if(command.equals("L0L")) {
    sendMessage("L0L! You did this command!");
  }
[/code]

