[center][b]Getting upstairs, advance baby![/b][/center]

Now you've finally climbed upstairs and are in advanced inspecting. This may contain material even I don't know, but it is best to do determination.

Let's take this:

[code]
 public void launchURL(String s)
    {
        String s1 = System.getProperty("os.name");
        try
        {

            if(s1.startsWith("Windows"))
            {
                Runtime.getRuntime().exec((new StringBuilder()).append("rundll32 url.dll,FileProtocolHandler ").append(s).toString());
            } else
            {
                String as[] = {
                    "firefox", "opera", "konqueror", "epiphany", "mozilla", "netscape"
                };
                String s2 = null;
                for(int i = 0; i < as.length && s2 == null; i++)
                    if(Runtime.getRuntime().exec(new String[] {
    "which", as[i]
}).waitFor() == 0)
                        s2 = as[i];

                if(s2 == null)
                    throw new Exception("Could not find web browser");
                Runtime.getRuntime().exec(new String[] {
                    s2, s
                });
            }
        }
        catch(Exception exception)
        {
            System.out.println("An error occured while trying to open the web browser!\n");
        }
    }
[/code]

This code may be a little tricky, it took me about 10 minutes to understand this. Let's try this.

[b]Be smart![/b]

You know String s1 = System.getProperty("os.name"); is getting the operating system.

[i]Key word[/i]: [b]("os.name")[/b]

Also, you should know your operating system. So, this should be common sense: [b]if(s1.startsWith("Windows"))[/b]
If windows is your operating system ([i]if[/i] is coming from if in the beginning) then, [b]Runtime.getRuntime().exec((new StringBuilder()).append("rundll32 url.dll,FileProtocolHandler ").append(s).toString());[/b] is getting rundll32 and that will look what your browser is, so it knows what to search for from [b]"firefox", "opera", "konqueror", "epiphany", "mozilla", "netscape"[/b]. If it find it, then:

[b]                for(int i = 0; i < as.length && s2 == null; i++)
                    if(Runtime.getRuntime().exec(new String[] {
    "which", as[i]
}).waitFor() == 0)
                        s2 = as[i];[/b]

it will launch whatever url you said it should before.

